;BACKSEAT (Holodeck Program)
NUMBER 3477
NAME Backseat
REGION 1
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CAFE
MOVEMENT_ASTRAL
CHANNEL 777

CALL 49

RELOGIN 1920

ITEM 0 1802
ITEM 1 249

IFVAR POSITION = 0
   POSITION LAY
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START
The lights in the distance twinkle in the darkness as you gaze down upon the
slumbering city far below your position in the leather backseat of this 1965
Mustang. Looking out the front windshield you can see the stars reflecting in
the candy apple red finish of the hood. The sounds of rock and roll emanate
from the eight track tape player in the dashboard, muffling the sounds of
various couplings from other cars parked nearby.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
Upholstered in burgundy leather, you are surprised at its smooth softness.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB LEAN 0
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR POSITION = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You lean back in the seat.
      ECHO OTHERS %N leans back in the seat.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You roll on your side and prop your head up on your elbow.
      ECHO OTHERS %N rolls on %h side and props %h head up on %h elbow.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB ROLL 0
   IFVAR POSITION = 2
      CLEARVERB
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
         ECHO PLAYER You roll over on your back.
         ECHO OTHERS %N rolls over on %h back.
         EQUAL FLAG2 0
      ENDIF
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
         ECHO PLAYER You roll over on your stomach.
         ECHO OTHERS %N rolls over on %h stomach.
         EQUAL FLAG2 1
      ENDIF
      EQUAL FLAG1 FLAG2
      EQUAL FLAG2 0
   ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
You can barely make out the vague shapes of other cars through the darkness
of night. A few of them seem to be rocking back-and-forth.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB ROLL 1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 0
      ECHO PLAYER You roll down the window.
      ECHO OTHERS %N rolls down the window.
      EQUAL ITEMVAL2 1
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You roll up the window.
      ECHO OTHERS %N rolls up the window.
      EQUAL ITEMVAL2 0
   ENDIF
   EQUAL ITEMVAL1 ITEMVAL2
   EQUAL ITEMVAL2 0
ENDIF

IFPREVERB TOUCH 1
   CLEARVERB
   RANDOM DUMMY1 1 3 0
   IFVAR DUMMY1 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You draw an obscene picture on the steamed-up window.
      ECHO OTHERS %N draws an obscene picture on the steamed-up window.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR DUMMY1 = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You draw a cute smily face on the steamed-up window.
      ECHO OTHERS %N draws a cute smily face on the steamed-up window.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR DUMMY1 = 3
      ECHO PLAYER You scribble the words "%N was here" on the steamed-up window.
      ECHO OTHERS %N scribbles the words "%N was here" on the steamed-up window.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LICK 1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You lick at the moisture that has collected on the windows.
   ECHO OTHERS %N licks at the moisture that has collected on the windows.
ENDIF

IFVERB LICK -1
   RANDOM DUMMY1 1 5 0
   IFVAR DUMMY1 = 2
      PLREVENT 2
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL The windows steam up a bit.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFVERB KISS -1
   RANDOM DUMMY1 1 5 0
   IFVAR DUMMY1 = 2
      PLREVENT 2
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL The windows steam up a bit.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LAY -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR POSITION = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You lay down on the seat.
      ECHO OTHERS %N lays down beside you.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You're already laying down.
   ENDIF
   POSITION LAY
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SIT -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR POSITION = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You sit up in the seat.
      ECHO OTHERS %N sits up in the seat.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You are already sitting.
   ENDIF
   POSITION SIT
ENDIF

IFPREVERB KNEEL -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER There's not enough room to kneel here.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB STAND -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You attempt to stand up, and bump your head on the roof of the car.
   ECHO OTHERS %N attempts to stand up, and bumps %h head on the roof of the car.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LISTEN -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You hear your favorite songs of the early seventies and your thoughts turn
      ECHO PLAYER to pleasant memories of the past.
      ECHO OTHERS %N listens closely to the music for a moment.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GAZE -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
      ECHO PLAYER You gaze out through the windshield at the nightscap beyond.
      ECHO OTHERS %N gazes through the windshield.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SMELL -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You sniff and smell the genuine leather upholstery.
      ECHO OTHERS %N sniffs.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY LEAVE_PROGRAM
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM < 2
      ECHO PLAYER A soft voice from nowhere in tones, "You are on the only inhabitant of this
      ECHO PLAYER holodeck program. To leave, please say END PROGRAM and then exit the holodeck.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 1
      ECHO PLAYER A swirling light begins to surround you. When it fades, you find you are no
      ECHO PLAYER longer where you were before...
      ECHO OTHERS A swirling light begins to surround %N. When it fades, %s is no longer there.
      MOVE 1920
      AFFECT 1920
      ECHO OTHERS You hear a low hum, and then %N appears surrounded by a swirling light that soon fades.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY END_PROGRAM
   ECHO ALL The scene fades instantly away...
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   EQUAL EXIT 3477
