ENDIF
;
;
;BARN LOFT (Holodeck Program)
NUMBER 3478
NAME Barn loft
REGION 1
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CAFE
MOVEMENT_ASTRAL
CHANNEL 777

CALL 49

RELOGIN 1920

*DESCRIPTION_START
The crowing of a rooster momentarily breaks the silence of this already warm
summer morning. A gentle neighing and a low moo in the distance respond to the
piercing greeting as golden sunlight begins to seep through the cracks in this
wooden barn. Fresh hay, its newly harvested scent still sweet in the air, is
mounded everywhere in deep piles as well as strewn about to cover the earthen
floor. Leather harnesses and reins hang forgotten on metal hooks pounded into
the sturdy wooden beams bearing the weight of the high peaked roof.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 0 1121 
ITEM 1 1122 ADJ1=222 ADJ2=272
ITEM 2 1842 ADJ1=415 ADJ2=180

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The hay forms a comfortable bed with its sweetness and softness lulling you.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
You see a rusty old metal hook pounded into the sturdy wooden beams, a worn
leather harness hanging from it.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
The harness is old and worn. You trust that it hasn't been used in ages.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB GET 2
   ECHO PLAYER You really have no use for that, since there aren't any horses around at the
   ECHO PLAYER moment. You decide to leave it where it is.
   ECHO OTHERS %n contemplates taking the harness, but changes %h mind.
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PULL 2
   ECHO PLAYER With a sly grin you show the harness to your friend.
   ECHO OTHERS %n shows you the harness with a sly grin on %h face.
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF 
   
IFPREVERB PULL 1
   ECHO PLAYER You discover the hook is sturdy enough to support your weight.
   ECHO OTHERS %n grabs on to the hook and hangs from it.
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PUSH 0
   ECHO PLAYER You push some hay around to form a soft pile.
   ECHO OTHERS %n pushes some hay around until %s forms a soft pile.
   CLEARVERB  
ENDIF 

IFPREVERB LICK 0
   ECHO PLAYER You decide to taste some hay. Now wasn't that silly?
   ECHO OTHERS %n puts some hay in %h mouth and tastes it. %H expression is priceless.      
   CLEARVERB 
ENDIF  

IFPREVERB LEAN 0
   ECHO PLAYER You bury yourself within the pile of hay!
   ECHO OTHERS You notice %n trying to hide %iself in the hay.
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF 
 
IFPREVERB KICK 0
   ECHO PLAYER You scatter the hay!
   ECHO OTHERS %n kicks the hay and scatters it everywhere! 
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF  

IFPREVERB GET 0
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 1
      ECHO PLAYER You take some hay and throw it at your friend!
      ECHO OTHERS %n throws some hay at you!
   ENDIF
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM < 2
      ECHO PLAYER You toss some hay up in the air and it comes floating back down, landing in
      ECHO PLAYER your hair.
   ENDIF
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF  

IFPREVERB EAT 0
   ECHO PLAYER Do you really want to do that with all the animals around here?
   ECHO OTHERS %n picks up some hay, looks thoughtful and drops it again.
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF
  
IFPREVERB LIGHT 0
   ECHO PLAYER As you light a match, Smokey the Bear comes in and lectures you.
   ECHO OTHERS As %N lights a match, Smokey the Bear comes in and says to %i, "Only YOU can prevent forest fires."
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF       

IFPREVERB PULL 0
   ECHO PLAYER You pull another bale of hay over.
   ECHO OTHERS %n pulls over another bale of hay.
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SIT -1
   ECHO PLAYER You sit down on a pile of soft hay.
   ECHO OTHERS %n has a seat in a pile of hay.
   CLEARVERB 
   POSITION SIT
ENDIF 

IFPREVERB TAP -1
   ECHO PLAYER You tap your foot on the sturdy wooden floor.
   ECHO OTHERS %n taps %h foot on the floor causing the animals in the barn to stir.
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF  

IFPREVERB SNIFF -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The sweet smell of hay tickles your nose.
   ECHO OTHERS %N's nose starts to twitch a little.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LISTEN -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You hear soft rustling sounds around you.
      ECHO OTHERS %N looks thoughtful.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB RECALL -1
   ECHO PLAYER You reflect on carefree days with no responsibility.
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LAY -1
   ECHO PLAYER You lie down on the soft hay.
   ECHO OTHERS %n lies down on the soft hay.
   CLEARVERB
   POSITION LAY
ENDIF

IFPREVERB JUMP -1
   ECHO PLAYER You jump into a huge pile of hay!  
   ECHO OTHERS You watch as %n jumps into a big pile of hay!  
   CLEARVERB
   POSITION SIT
ENDIF     

IFPREVERB ROLL 0
   ECHO PLAYER You decide you can't resist the urge any longer and roll around in the hay!
   ECHO OTHERS %N rolls around in the hay! You have a strong desire to join %i.
   CLEARVERB  
   POSITION LAY
ENDIF

IFSAY LEAVE_PROGRAM
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM < 2
      ECHO PLAYER A soft voice from nowhere in tones, "You are on the only inhabitant of this
      ECHO PLAYER holodeck program. To leave, please say END PROGRAM and then exit the holodeck.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 1
      ECHO PLAYER A swirling light begins to surround you. When it fades, you find you are no
      ECHO PLAYER longer where you were before...
      ECHO OTHERS A swirling light begins to surround %N. When it fades, %s is no longer there.
      MOVE 1920
      AFFECT 1920
      ECHO OTHERS You hear a low hum, and then %N appears surrounded by a swirling light that soon fades.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY END_PROGRAM
   ECHO ALL The scene fades instantly away...
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   EQUAL EXIT 3478
   CALL 38
ENDIF
