;CABIN HIDEAWAY (Holodeck Program)
NUMBER 3479
NAME Cabin Hideaway
REGION 1
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CAFE
MOVEMENT_ASTRAL
CHANNEL 777

CALL 49

RELOGIN 1920

ITEM 0 249
ITEM 1 343
ITEM 2 196
ITEM 3 85 ADJ1=178 ADJ2=32
ITEM 4 1304 ADJ1=222 ADJ2=728
ITEM 5 362 ADJ1=138
ITEM 6 378 ADJ1=165 CLOSED
ITEM 7 193 ADJ1=367 ADJ2=493
ITEM 8 1770 ADJ1=493

*DESCRIPTION_START
The howling wind rattles the shutters outside the frost covered windows of
this small wooden cabin. A fire blazes merrily inside the stone hearth, staving
off the bitter cold and filling the air with the scent of burning pine. The
cozy mountain hideaway shudders with each blast of the raging storm outside. A
large brass bed piled high with soft plump pillows stands against the far wall,
creaking softly in the draft. Basking in the warmth of the glowing fire is an
old tattered sofa and a soft fur rug.
*DESCRIPTION_END

; FLAG1 = 0 SOFA
; FLAG1 = 1 RUG
; FLAG1 = 2 BED

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
A layer of frost covers the clouded, uneven panes of glass on the outside.
On the inside, a coating of steam further enhances their opacity.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFTOUCH 0
   IFVAR POSITION ! 0
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You can't reach the window from here.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB TOUCH 0
   IFVAR POSITION = 0
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You begin drawing silly pictures on the steamed up window with your finger.
      ECHO OTHERS %N begins drawing silly pictures on the steamed up window with %h finger.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
Not a work of masonary excellence, the bricks of this small hearth are a bit
haphazard in the way they lay. Here and there, bulges of hardened mortar
protrude from the grouting. Still it serves it purpose, spewing heat into the
drafty room.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFTOUCH 1
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
      IFVAR POSITION ! 0
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER You can't reach the hearth from here.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You can't reach the hearth from here.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB TOUCH 1
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
      IFVAR POSITION = 0
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER You reach out toward the hearth and warm your hands by the fire.
         ECHO OTHERS %N reaches out toward the hearth and warms %h hands by the fire.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You reach out toward the hearth and warm your hands by the fire.
      ECHO OTHERS %N reaches out toward the hearth and warms %h hands by the fire.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB POKE 1
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
      IFVAR POSITION = 0
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER Using the poker, you carefully move some of the blazing logs, stoking the
         ECHO PLAYER blazing fire.
         ECHO OTHERS %N tends the fire with a poker.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER Using the poker, you carefully move some of the blazing logs, stoking the
      ECHO PLAYER blazing fire.
      ECHO OTHERS %N tends the fire with a poker.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
The logs are a bit greener than you'd like, smoking and hissing as they burn.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFTOUCH 2
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
      IFVAR POSITION ! 0
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER You can't reach the logs from here.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You can't reach the logs from here.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GET 2
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
      IFVAR POSITION = 0
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER You pick up a log and add it to the little hearth.
         ECHO OTHERS %N adds another log to the blazing hearth.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You pick up a log and add it to the little hearth.
      ECHO OTHERS %N adds another log to the blazing hearth.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
Covered by a warm goose down quilt and piles of soft plump pillows, the old
fashioned feather bed is fluffed. A little too far from the fire, it is never
the less the warmest place in the room for two.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFTOUCH 3
   IFVAR FLAG1 ! 2
      IFVAR POSITION ! 0
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER You can't reach the bed from here.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 3
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You are already in bed.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG1 ! 2
      ECHO PLAYER You walk over to the bed and hop in.
      ECHO OTHERS %N walks over to the bed and hops in.
      EQUAL FLAG1 2
      POSITION LAY
   ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
In another era it was a probably a fine piece of upholstered furniture, fit
to grace the finest room. However, that was a very long time ago. Relegated in
its retirement to this rustic abode, it serves well as a comfortable place to
sit and be close to the fire.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFTOUCH 4
   IFVAR FLAG1 ! 0
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You can't reach the sofa from here.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 5
The fur rug came from the back of a bear. The deep pile is warm and inviting
from its position so close to the fire.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFTOUCH 5
   IFVAR FLAG1 ! 1
      IFVAR POSITION ! 0
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER You can't reach the fur rug from here.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 5
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You stroll over to the fur rug and plop down on top of it, relaxing in the
   ECHO PLAYER warmth of the stone hearth.
   ECHO OTHERS %N strolls over to the fur rug and plops down on top of it.
   EQUAL FLAG1 1
   POSITION LAY
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 6
A little battered, but still in good working order, the ice box hums away.
Some how it seems silly to keep things in it when just outside the door is the
gigantic natural ice box the fire is working so hard to keep at bay.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFTOUCH 6
   IFVAR FLAG1 ! 0
      IFVAR POSITION ! 0
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER You can't reach the ice box from here.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB OPEN 6
   CLEARVERB
   IFITEM 9
      ECHO PLAYER You go to get another bottle of beer, but there is already one out. You'll
      ECHO PLAYER need to pick it up first.
   ENDIF
   IFNOITEM 9
      ECHO PLAYER You open the ice box and set out a bottle of beer.
      ECHO OTHERS %N opens the ice box and sets out a bottle of beer.
      NEWITEM 9 158 ADJ1=152 VAL5=9
      NEWPUT 9 1562 ADJ1=61 VAL2=10
   ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 7
The pillow is fluffed and plump, ready for a weary head.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFTOUCH 7
   IFVAR FLAG1 ! 2
      IFVAR POSITION ! 0
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER You can't reach the pillow from here.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GET 7
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
      IFVAR POSITION = 0
         CLEARVERB
         IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 1
            ECHO PLAYER You grab the pillow and start smacking others in the head with it!
            ECHO OTHERS %N grabs the pillow and starts smacking you in the head with it!
         ENDIF
         IFVAR PLRSINROOM = 1
            ECHO PLAYER As you grab the pillow, you wish there was someone else here to smack with it.
         ENDIF
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
      CLEARVERB
      IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 1
         ECHO PLAYER You grab the pillow and start smacking others in the head with it!
         ECHO OTHERS %N grabs the pillow and starts smacking you in the head with it!
      ENDIF
      IFVAR PLRSINROOM = 1
         ECHO PLAYER As you grab the pillow, you wish there was someone else here to smack with it.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PULL 7
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
      IFVAR POSITION = 0
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER You begin pulling the stuffing out of the pillow!
         ECHO OTHERS %N begins wrestling around with the pillow.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You begin pulling the stuffing out of the pillow!
      ECHO OTHERS %N begins wrestling around with the pillow.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PUSH 7
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You scrunch up the pillow and wedge it beneath your head.
      ECHO OTHERS %N scrunches up the pillow and wedges it beneath %h head.
      POSITION LAY
   ENDIF
ENDIF
   
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 8
The quilt is very soft and warm, filled with luxurious down held in by a 
patchwork of multi-colored soft cotten squares.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFTOUCH 8
   IFVAR FLAG1 ! 2
      IFVAR POSITION ! 0
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER You can't reach the quilt from here.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PULL 8
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
      IFVAR POSITION = 0
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER You try to pull the quilt off the bed, but it won't budge.
         ECHO OTHERS %N tries, without success, to pull the quilt off the bed.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You pull the quilt up around you and snuggle into the bed.
      ECHO OTHERS %N pulls the quilt up around %i and snuggles into the bed.
      POSITION LAY
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SMELL -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER The room smells old like an attic, a warm friendly mixture of mustiness and
      ECHO PLAYER mold with a touch of pine smoke from the sputtering fire.
      ECHO OTHERS %N sniffs.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LISTEN -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You listen to the fury of the snow storm banging against the old cabin, its
      ECHO PLAYER shutters rattling loudly.
      ECHO OTHERS %N stops to listen to the storm for a minute.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB JUMP -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You climb on to the bed and begin jumping up and down like a kid for a bit.
   ECHO PLAYER Then feeling a bit silly, you let yourself drop into its warm softness.
   ECHO OTHERS %N climbs on to the bed and begins jumping up and down like a kid. After a moment, %s looks a little
bashfull and then plops down on to the bed.
   POSITION LAY
   EQUAL FLAG1 2
ENDIF

IFPREVERB ROLL -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR FLAG2 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You roll on to your back.
      ECHO OTHERS %N rolls on to %h back.
      EQUAL FLAG3 0
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG2 = 0
      ECHO PLAYER You roll on to your stomach.
      ECHO OTHERS %N rolls on to %h stomach.
      EQUAL FLAG3 1
   ENDIF
   EQUAL FLAG2 FLAG3
   EQUAL FLAG3 0
ENDIF

IFPREVERB STAND -1
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You roll out of bed.
      ECHO OTHERS %N rolls out of bed.
      POSITION STAND
   ENDIF
   EQUAL FLAG1 0
   EQUAL FLAG2 0
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LAY -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR POSITION = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You're already lying down.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION ! 2
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
         ECHO PLAYER You lay back on the fur rug.
         ECHO OTHERS %N lays back on the fur rug.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
         ECHO PLAYER You lay back in bed.
         ECHO OTHERS %n lays back in bed.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
         IFVAR POSITION ! 0
            ECHO PLAYER You lay back on the sofa.
            ECHO OTHERS %N lays back on the sofa.
         ENDIF
         IFVAR POSITION = 0
            ECHO PLAYER You lay down on the fur rug in front of the hearth.
            ECHO OTHERS %N lays down on the fur rug in front of the hearth.
            EQUAL FLAG2 1
         ENDIF
      ENDIF
      POSITION LAY
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SIT -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR POSITION = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You're already sitting down.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION ! 1
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
         ECHO PLAYER You sit down on the fur rug.
         ECHO OTHERS %N sits down on the fur rug.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
         ECHO PLAYER You sit up in bed.
         ECHO OTHERS %n sits up in bed.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
         IFVAR POSITION ! 0
            ECHO PLAYER You sit up on the sofa.
            ECHO OTHERS %N sit up on the sofa.
         ENDIF
         IFVAR POSITION = 0
            ECHO PLAYER You sit down on the fur rug in front of the hearth.
            ECHO OTHERS %N sits down on the fur rug in front of the hearth.
            EQUAL FLAG2 1
         ENDIF
      ENDIF
      POSITION SIT
      EQUAL FLAG2 0
   ENDIF
ENDIF
  
IFPREVERB KNEEL -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR POSITION = 3
      ECHO PLAYER You're already kneeling.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION ! 3
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
         ECHO PLAYER You kneel on the fur rug.
         ECHO OTHERS %N kneels on the fur rug.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
         ECHO PLAYER You want to kneel on a bed?
      ENDIF
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
         IFVAR POSITION = 0
            ECHO PLAYER You kneel down on the fur rug in front of the hearth.
            ECHO OTHERS %N kneels down on the fur rug in front of the hearth.
            EQUAL FLAG1 1
         ENDIF
         IFVAR POSITION ! 0
            ECHO PLAYER You want to kneel on a sofa?
         ENDIF
      ENDIF
      POSITION KNEEL
      EQUAL FLAG2 0
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY LEAVE_PROGRAM
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM < 2
      ECHO PLAYER A soft voice from nowhere in tones, "You are on the only inhabitant of this
      ECHO PLAYER holodeck program. To leave, please say END PROGRAM and then exit the holodeck.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 1
      ECHO PLAYER A swirling light begins to surround you. When it fades, you find you are no
      ECHO PLAYER longer where you were before...
      ECHO OTHERS A swirling light begins to surround %N. When it fades, %s is no longer there.
      MOVE 1920
      AFFECT 1920
      ECHO OTHERS You hear a low hum, and then %N appears surrounded by a swirling light that soon fades.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY END_PROGRAM
   ECHO ALL The scene fades instantly away...
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   EQUAL EXIT 3479
   CALL 38
ENDIF
