;
;FERN GROTTO (Holodeck Program)
NUMBER 3480
NAME Fern Grotto
REGION 1
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CAFE
MOVEMENT_ASTRAL
CHANNEL 777

CALL 49

RELOGIN 1920

ITEM 0 324 ADJ1=56 ADJ2=77 ADJ3=29
ITEM 1 198 ADJ1=56 ADJ2=77 ADJ3=29 VAL2=100
ITEM 2 661 ADJ1=152
ITEM 3 411 ADJ1=297
ITEM 4 380 ADJ1=294 ADJ2=658
ITEM 5 367 ADJ1=297 ADJ2=491
EXTEND 5 laying just beneath the surface of the water

;flag1 = 1 (in pool)
;flag1 = 0 (not in pool)

*DESCRIPTION_START
Silvery moonbeams stream in from the open ceiling to play and sparkle upon the
surface of a crystal clear blue pool. The sound of water trickling down the
moss covered stone walls echoes through the grotto in a soft cachaphoney. The
entire area, every nook and cranny, every inch of the soft earth floor, sports
a profusion of lacey green ferns bending gracefully in the shimmering light.
Smooth rock steps lead down into the beckoning pool.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The pool is fed by a tiny hotspring. The water emerges from a small fissure
above your head and runs no faster than a trickle, cooling as it runs down the
rock wall. There is very little algae to cloud the water, probably due to the
appetite of the small fish living here.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB GAZE 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You gaze into the pool.
   ECHO OTHERS %N gazes into the pool.
   RANDOM DUMMY1 1 20 0
   IFVAR DUMMY1 = 20
      PLREVENT 2
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO PLAYER You reflection in the pool suddenly changes into that of someone you have
      ECHO PLAYER never seen before in your life.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 0
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You're already in the pool.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
      ECHO PLAYER Your body glides effortlessly through the warm water as you carefully step
      ECHO PLAYER down the rocks into the pool, breaking the glassy surface with gentle ripples.
      ECHO PLAYER Looking down through the crystal pool you can see small silvery fish nibbling
      ECHO PLAYER at the air bubbles that cling to your toes. The indentations on the tops of
      ECHO PLAYER several smooth flat boulders resting just below the surface of the water seem
      ECHO PLAYER to have been made intentionally as a place to lie and enjoy the traquility of
      ECHO PLAYER this lush grotto.
      ECHO OTHERS %N steps down the rocks into the pool.
      EQUAL FLAG1 1
   ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The luke warm water of the pool is filled with miniscule fish. Their silvery
skin reflects the moonlight, creating the effect of hundreds of tiny shimmering
rainbows.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB GAZE 1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You gaze into the pool.
   ECHO OTHERS %N gazes into the pool.
   RANDOM DUMMY1 1 20 0
   IFVAR DUMMY1 = 20
      PLREVENT 2
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO PLAYER You reflection in the pool suddenly changes into that of someone you have
      ECHO PLAYER never seen before in your life.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You're already in the pool.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
      ECHO PLAYER Your body glides effortlessly through the warm water as you carefully step
      ECHO PLAYER down the rocks into the pool, breaking the glassy surface with gentle ripples.
      ECHO PLAYER Looking down through the crystal pool you can see small silvery fish nibbling
      ECHO PLAYER at the air bubbles that cling to your toes. The indentations on the tops of
      ECHO PLAYER several smooth flat boulders resting just below the surface of the water seem
      ECHO PLAYER to have been made intentionally as a place to lie and enjoy the traquility of
      ECHO PLAYER this lush grotto.
      ECHO OTHERS %N steps down the rocks into the pool.
      EQUAL FLAG1 1
   ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
The lacey green ferns grow every which way out of the soft earth. You notice
their fractal nature as each branch divides into more branches.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFTOUCH 2
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You can't reach the ferns from the pool.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB TOUCH 2
   IFVAR FLAG1 ! 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You run your fingers through the soft green ferns.
      ECHO OTHERS %N runs %h fingers through the soft green ferns.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 2
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
      ECHO PLAYER You lie down in the ferns.
      ECHO OTHERS %N lies down in the ferns.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You get out of the pool and lie down in the ferns.
      ECHO OTHERS %n gets out of the pool and lies down in the ferns.
      EQUAL FLAG1 0
   ENDIF
   POSITION LAY
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
The rocks are smooth, though the evidence is that they were once part of the
ceiling that gave away and is now open to the sky. They have been worn down by
the flowing water over the eons.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB TOUCH 3
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You run your fingers across the smooth rocks.
   ECHO OTHERS %N runs %h fingers across the smooth rocks.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB KICK 3
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You stub your toe on a rock!
   ECHO OTHERS %N stubs %h toe on a rock!
ENDIF

IFPREVERB ROLL 3
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You rock and roll!
   ECHO OTHERS %N starts strumming an invisible guitar.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 3
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
      ECHO PLAYER Your body glides effortlessly through the warm water as you carefully step
      ECHO PLAYER down the rocks into the pool, breaking the glassy surface with gentle ripples.
      ECHO PLAYER Looking down through the crystal pool you can see small silvery fish nibbling
      ECHO PLAYER at the air bubbles that cling to your toes. The indentations on the tops of
      ECHO PLAYER several smooth flat boulders resting just below the surface of the water seem
      ECHO PLAYER to have been made intentionally as a place to lie and enjoy the traquility of
      ECHO PLAYER this lush grotto.
      ECHO OTHERS %N steps down the rocks into the grotto pool.
      EQUAL FLAG2 1
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You climb the rocks out of the grotto pool.
      ECHO OTHERS %N climbs the rocks out of the grotto pool.
      EQUAL FLAG2 0
   ENDIF
   EQUAL FLAG1 FLAG2
   EQUAL FLAG2 0
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
The tiny fish swim back and forth in the crystal blue pool, sometimes coming
up to the smooth rocks for a closer look, but then immediately darting back out
into the deeper waters.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFTOUCH 4
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
      ECHO PLAYER The fish are in the water. And you aren't. 
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER They avoid you.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB2 PUT 4
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER Interesting concept.
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 5
Lying just beneath the surface of the water, these smooth flat boulders are
the perfect place to lie and lanquish in the tranquility of this lush grotto.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFTOUCH 5
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER The boulders lie just beneath the surface of the water in the grotto pool.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 5
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
      CLEARVERB
      IFVAR POSITION = 0
         ECHO PLAYER You take a seat on one of the boulders that lies just beneath the surface of
         ECHO PLAYER the water.
         ECHO OTHERS %N takes a seat on one of the boulders that lies just beneath the surface of the water.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR POSITION ! 0
         ECHO PLAYER You're already on one of the boulders.
      ENDIF
      POSITION SIT
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SMELL -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You sniff and catch the scent of jasmine drifting in the still air.
      ECHO OTHERS %N sniffs.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LISTEN -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You focus your attention on the sounds of the dripping water for a moment.
      ECHO OTHERS %N listens.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB KICK 1
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You push off and swim across the pool.
      ECHO OTHERS %N pushes off and swims across the pool.
      POSITION STAND
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SLAP 1
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You paddle out into the middle of the pool.
      ECHO OTHERS %N paddles out into the center of the pool.
      POSITION STAND
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB JUMP -1
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You take a running jump into the grotto pool, splashing water everywhere.
      ECHO OTHERS %N takes a running jump into the grotto pool, spashing you with water.
      EQUAL FLAG1 1
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SPIT -1
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You take in a mouthful of water and shoot it out in an arching spout.
      ECHO OTHERS %N takes in a mouthful of water and shoots it out in an arching spout.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB OUT -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You climb the rocks out of the grotto pool.
   ECHO OTHERS %N climbs the rocks out of the grotto pool.
   EQUAL FLAG1 0
   POSITION STAND
ENDIF

IFPREVERB KNEEL -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER There's really no place to kneel here.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SIT -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
      IFVAR POSITION = 0
         ECHO PLAYER You sit down on a smooth rock.
         ECHO OTHERS %N sits down on a smooth rock.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR POSITION = 1
         ECHO PLAYER You're already sitting.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR POSITION = 2
         ECHO PLAYER You sit up.
         ECHO OTHERS %N sits up.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR POSITION = 3
         ECHO PLAYER You sit down on a smooth rock.
         ECHO OTHERS %n sits down on a smooth rock.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
      IFVAR POSITION = 0
         ECHO PLAYER You take a seat on one of the boulders that lies just beneath the surface of
         ECHO PLAYER the water.
         ECHO OTHERS %N takes a seat on one of the boulders that lies just beneath the surface of the water.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR POSITION = 1
         ECHO PLAYER You're already sitting.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR POSITION = 2
         ECHO PLAYER You sit up.
         ECHO OTHERS %N sits up.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR POSITION = 3
         ECHO PLAYER You take a seat on one of the boulders that lies just beneath the surface of
         ECHO PLAYER the water.
         ECHO OTHERS %N takes a seat on one of the boulders that lies just beneath the surface of the water.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
   POSITION SIT
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LAY -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
      IFVAR POSITION = 0
         ECHO PLAYER You lay down on the ferns.
         ECHO OTHERS %N lays down on the ferns.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR POSITION = 1
         ECHO PLAYER You lay back in the ferns.
         ECHO OTHERS %N lays back in the ferns.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR POSITION = 2
         ECHO PLAYER You're already laying down.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR POSITION = 3
         ECHO PLAYER You lay back in the ferns.
         ECHO OTHERS %N lays back in the ferns.
      ENDIF
