;
;ISLAND BEACH (Holodeck Program)
NUMBER 3481
NAME Island Beach
REGION 1
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CAFE
MOVEMENT_ASTRAL
CHANNEL 777

CALL 49

RELOGIN 1920

ITEM 0 413 ADJ1=162 ADJ2=635
PUT 0 433 ADJ1=425 ADJ2=143 VAL5=9
ITEM 1 198 ADJ1=67 ADJ2=29 VAL2=100
ITEM 2 86 ADJ1=1227
ITEM 3 665 ADJ1=183
ITEM 4 229 ADJ1=1149

*DESCRIPTION_START
Swirls of brillant orange and vibrant yellow paint the sky with wide swaths of
color as a smoldering red sun sinks into the horizon. The long arched fronds of
tall palm trees rustle in the cool ocean breezes which caress this small island
surrounded by a placid crystal clear blue sea. Smooth pieces of colorful glass,
rounded by warm ocean currents, are washed ashore in the gently cresting waves.
The soft sand glitters in the fading rays of the sun, its comfortable surface
warm and inviting.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
When you look very closely at the sand, you can see a tiny rainbow reflected
in every transluscent grain.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB PLAY 0
   CLEARVERB
   EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
   IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 0
      NEWITEM 5 916 ADJ1=455
      ECHO PLAYER You begin to make a sand castle by carefully pushing the sand into a mound.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL5 > 0
      IFVAR ITEMVAL5 < 4
         ECHO PLAYER You continue to enlarge a sand mound by piling more and more sand on top.
         ECHO OTHERS %N continues to enlarge a mound of sand by piling more and more sand on top.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 4
      ECHO PLAYER You add the final load to what is now a very large mound of sand.
      ECHO OTHERS %N adds the final load to what is now a very large mound of sand.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 5
       ECHO PLAYER You begin the process of carving out a castle from the mound.
       ECHO OTHERS %N begins the process of carving out a castle from the mound.
       REMOVEITEM 5
       NEWITEM 5 1211 ADJ3=455
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 6
       ECHO PLAYER You carefully edge what will be the ramparts with crenelations.
       ECHO OTHERS %N carefully edges what will be the ramparts with crenalations.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 7
       ECHO PLAYER You shape jagged towers at the corners of the battlements and put tiny windows in them with your
little finger.
       ECHO OTHERS %N shapes jagged towers at the corners of the battlements and put tiny windows in them with %h
little finger.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 8
       ECHO PLAYER You dig a trench around the new castle to serve as a moat.
       ECHO OTHERS %N digs a trench around the castle to serve as a moat.
       SETITEMVAL 5 5 8
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 9
       SETITEMADJ 5 2 663
       ECHO PLAYER The sand castle is finished. You stand back to admire it.
       ECHO OTHERS %N stands back and admires the finished sand castle.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL5 < 9
       ADD ITEMVAL5 1
       SETITEMVAL 5 5 ITEMVAL5
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GET 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You scoop up a handful of the warm silky feeling sand and drizzle it slowly
   ECHO PLAYER through your fingers.
   ECHO OTHERS %N scoops up a handful of sand and drizzles it slowly through %h fingers.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SLAP 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO OTHERS %N throws sand at you.
   ECHO PLAYER You pick up some sand and toss it around.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB KICK 0
   ECHO PLAYER You kick up some sand.
   ECHO OTHERS %N kicks up some sand nearly blinding you.
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PUSH 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You dig your feet into the silky sand, letting its smooth warmth seep around
   ECHO PLAYER your toes.
   ECHO OTHERS %N digs %h feet into the sand.
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
You're not quite sure, but as you look into the clear blue water you think
you catch a glimpse of an exotic orange fish hiding in a reef just below the
surface.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM IN 1
You see a big orange fish staring back at you.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB DRINK 1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO OTHERS %N makes an ugly face after taking a sip of the salty sea water.
   ECHO PLAYER The water is salty!
ENDIF

IFPREVERB TOUCH 1
   ECHO PLAYER You reach out and touch the water, feeling its gentle warmth.
   ECHO OTHERS %N tests the water temperature.
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You wade into the cool blue water, splashing around a bit, and then return
   ECHO PLAYER to the beach.
   ECHO OTHERS %N wades into the water and splashes around a bit.
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
It's an everyday beach chair, straps pulled across an aluminum frame, with a
terry cloth covered cushion.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
The long fronds belong to a nearby queen palm.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
The queen palm tree sprouts beautifully drooping long full fronds from its
absolutely straight trunk.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB LOOK 5
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR ITEMVAL5 < 6
      ECHO PLAYER Its your basic piled up mound of sand. It would not take very much effort to
      ECHO PLAYER turn it into a splendid sand castle.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL5 > 5
      IFVAR ITEMVAL5 < 9
         ECHO PLAYER This is going to be a great castle when you finish it.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 9
         ECHO PLAYER It is a perfectly little castle with a moat around it. You can almost imagine tiny knights
walking around it battlements.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
   SETITEMVAL 0 5 ITEMVAL5
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GET 5
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You can't get that.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB KICK 5
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR ITEMVAL5 < 6
      ECHO PLAYER You kick some sand of the top of the mound making it much smaller.
      ECHO OTHERS %N kicks some sand off the top of the mound making it much smaller
      SUB ITEMVAL5 1 
      IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 0
         ECHO ALL The mound is utterly destroyed.
         REMOVEITEM 5
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL5 > 5
      ECHO PLAYER You kick %a turning it back into a mere mound of sand.
      ECHO OTHERS %N kicks %a turning it back into a mere mound of sand.
      REMOVEITEM 5
      NEWITEM 5 916 ADJ1=274 VAL5=5
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LISTEN -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You hear the squawk of gulls flying over the water.
      ECHO OTHERS %N listens %h surroundings.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SNIFF -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You detect the scent of salt and seaweed on the breeze.
   ECHO OTHERS %N sniffs.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB STAND -1
   EQUAL FLAG1 0
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SIT -1
   IFVAR POSITION = 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You take a seat on the on a lounge chair.
      ECHO OTHERS %N takes a seat on a lounge chair.
      POSITION SIT
      EQUAL FLAG1 0
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LAY -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR POSITION = 0
      ECHO PLAYER You lay down on the sand, stretching out, and letting your body catch the warming rays from the
everlasting sunset.
      ECHO OTHERS %N lays down and stretches out on the sand.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You relax in your lounge chair, reclining it back into a laying position.
      ECHO OTHERS %N relaxes in %h lounge chair, reclining it back into a laying position.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You're already laying.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 3
      ECHO PLAYER You lay down on the sand, stretching out, and letting your body catch the warming rays from the
everlasting sunset.
      ECHO OTHERS %N lays down and stretches out on the sand.
   ENDIF
   POSITION LAY
ENDIF

IFPREVERB ROLL -1
   IFVAR POSITION = 2
      CLEARVERB
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
         ECHO PLAYER You roll over onto your stomach.
         ECHO OTHERS %N rolls over onto %h stomach.
         EQUAL FLAG2 1
      ENDIF
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
         ECHO PLAYER You roll over onto your back.
         ECHO OTHERS %N rolls over onto %h back.
         EQUAL FLAG2 0
      ENDIF
      EQUAL FLAG1 FLAG2
      EQUAL FLAG2 0
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 0
