ITEM 2 198 VAL2=100
EXTEND 2 from the rushing river
ITEM 3 403 ADJ1=355
ITEM 4 1108 ADJ1=355 VAL2=3483
ITEM 5 881 ADJ1=163
EXTEND 5 draped with dangling pale green moss

*DESCRIPTION_START
Rushing water splashes loudly against this wooden deck that juts out into the
rapidly flowing river. Huge heavy limbed trees, draped with dangling pale green
moss, are barely visible through the darkness of night. Colored lanterns strung
between wooden beams brighten very little beyond the area of the deck itself.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The colorful string of lanterns provide a nice dim glow around the deck.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The old planks have been worn down with time, yet seem more than sturdy enough
to support any activity you wish to partake on it. You may want to watch your
step though, as the deck is very wet due to the spray from the rushing river.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
Gazing into the dark water reveals little of the depths below.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
You see a wooden raft tethered to one of the beams of the deck. It is sturdy
looking and seems to be of fine craftsmanship.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
The sturdy ladder leads down to the wooden raft.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 5
The huge heavy limbed trees are barely visible through the darkness. You can
just make out some pale green moss, which seems to almost glow in the light of
the moon, dangling from the tree limbs.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFTOUCH 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The lanterns are just out of reach.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LIGHT 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The lanterns are just out of reach.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB UNLIGHT 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The lanterns are just out of reach.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB KICK 1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR ROUNDTIME ! 0
      STRCVT 0 ROUNDTIME
      ECHO PLAYER [Wait %0 seconds...]
   ELSE
      EQUAL ROUNDTIME 6
      ECHO PLAYER You kick at a slippery board and lose your footing...
      ECHO OTHERS %N kicks at a slippery board and loses %h footing...
      PLREVENT 1
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO PLAYER You seem to hang in mid-air for a few seconds...
      ECHO OTHERS %S seems to hang in mid-air for a few seconds...
      PLREVENT 1
      CONTPLREVENT
      POSITION LAY
      ECHO PLAYER You land on your back with a thud!
      ECHO OTHERS %S lands on %h back with a thud!
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB TOUCH 2
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR POSITION = 0
      ECHO PLAYER You sit down and lazily dangle your feet in %a.
      ECHO OTHERS %N sits down and lazily dangles %h feet in %a.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You lazily dangle your feet in %a.
      ECHO OTHERS %N lazily dangles %h feet in %a.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You sit up and lazily dangle your feet in %a.
      ECHO OTHERS %N sits up and lazily dangles %h feet in the %a.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 3
      ECHO PLAYER You sit down and lazily dangle your feet in the clear blue water.
      ECHO OTHERS %N sits down and lazily dangles %h feet in the clear blue water.
   ENDIF
   POSITION SIT
ENDIF

IFPREVERB DRINK 2
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You cup your hands and take a drink of %a.
   ECHO OTHERS %N cups %h hands and takes a drink of %a.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 2
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You consider taking a swim in the dark waters of this rapidly rushing river,
   ECHO PLAYER but then decide it wouldn't be such a great idea. You notice a sturdy looking
   ECHO PLAYER raft tethered nearby.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 3
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You notice that the raft is several feet below the top of the deck, and you
   ECHO PLAYER don't think jumping would be such a great idea. But lucky for you, there is
   ECHO PLAYER a sturdy wooden ladder leading down the side of the deck.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB CLIMB 4
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You descend the ladder and climb aboard the sturdy raft.
   ECHO OTHERS %N climbs down the wooden ladder.
   DISBAND
   MOVE 3483
   AFFECT 3483
   ECHO OTHERS %N climbs aboard the raft.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 4
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You descend the ladder and climb aboard the sturdy raft.
   ECHO OTHERS %N climbs down the wooden ladder.
   DISBAND
   MOVE 3483
   AFFECT 3483
   ECHO OTHERS %N climbs aboard the raft.
ENDIF

IFTOUCH 5
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The trees are too far away.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LAY -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR POSITION = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You're already stretched out on the wooden deck.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION ! 2
      POSITION LAY
      ECHO PLAYER You stretch yourself out on the wooden deck, gazing up at a partially hidden
      ECHO PLAYER moon through the tree limbs.
      ECHO OTHERS %N stretches %iself out on the wooden deck and gazes up at the nighttime sky.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SIT -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR POSITION = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You're already sitting.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You sit up.
      ECHO OTHERS %N sits up.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 3
      ECHO PLAYER You take a seat on the wooden deck.
      ECHO OTHERS %N takes a seat on the wooden deck.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 0
      RANDOM DUMMY1 1 4 0
      IFVAR DUMMY1 = 1
         ECHO PLAYER As you take a seat on the wooden deck you yelp out in pain as a very sharp
         ECHO PLAYER splinter pokes you in the butt!
         ECHO OTHERS %N yelps out in pain as %s takes a seat on the wooden deck!
      ELSE
         ECHO PLAYER You take a seat on the wooden deck.
         ECHO OTHERS %N takes a seat on the wooden deck.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
   POSITION SIT
ENDIF

IFPREVERB JUMP -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR ROUNDTIME ! 0
      STRCVT 0 ROUNDTIME
      ECHO PLAYER [Wait %0 seconds...]
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ROUNDTIME = 0
      RANDOM DUMMY1 1 5 0
      IFVAR DUMMY1 > 3
         EQUAL ROUNDTIME 6
         ECHO PLAYER Jumping up and down, you land on a slippery board and lose your footing...
         ECHO OTHERS Jumping up and down, %N lands on a slippery board and loses %h footing...
         PLREVENT 1
         CONTPLREVENT
         ECHO PLAYER You seem to hang in mid-air for a few seconds...
         ECHO OTHERS %S seems to hang in mid-air for a few seconds...
         PLREVENT 1
         CONTPLREVENT
         POSITION LAY
         ECHO PLAYER You land on your back with a thud!
         ECHO OTHERS %S lands on %h back with a thud!
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY1 < 4
         ECHO PLAYER You jump up and down on the wooden deck.
         ECHO OTHERS %N jumps up and down on the wooden deck.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LISTEN -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER The sound of rushing water mingles with the quiet singing of the crickets.
      ECHO OTHERS %N listens to the music of the night.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SMELL -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You inhale the fresh clean scent in the air.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY LEAVE_PROGRAM
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM < 2
      ECHO PLAYER A soft voice from nowhere in tones, "You are on the only inhabitant of this
      ECHO PLAYER holodeck program. To leave, please say END PROGRAM and then exit the holodeck.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 1
      ECHO PLAYER A swirling light begins to surround you. When it fades, you find you are no
      ECHO PLAYER longer where you were before...
      ECHO OTHERS A swirling light begins to surround %N. When it fades, %s is no longer there.
      MOVE 1920
      AFFECT 1920
      ECHO OTHERS You hear a low hum, and then %N appears surrounded by a swirling light that soon fades.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY END_PROGRAM
   ECHO ALL The scene fades instantly away...
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   EQUAL EXIT 3482
   CALL 38
ENDIF
