;
;
;WESTERN SALOON (Holodeck Program)
NUMBER 3484
NAME Western Saloon
REGION 1
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CAFE
MOVEMENT_ASTRAL
CHANNEL 777

CALL 49

RELOGIN 1920

ITEM 0 1677 ADJ1=355
ITEM 1 1050 ADJ2=32
ITEM 2 1342 ADJ1=183 ADJ2=241 ADJ3=355
ITEM 3 204 ADJ1=227
ITEM 4 1676
ITEM 5 91 ADJ1=317
ITEM 7 529 ADJ1=961
ITEM 8 1279 ADJ2=32

STOREITEM 1562 -1 0
STOREITEM 1561 -1 0
STOREITEM 1560 -1 0

*DESCRIPTION_START
Muffled conversations, deep belly laughs, and clanking spurs resound through
this saloon. The smell of leather boots and chaps mingle with the strong aroma
of whiskey and beer emanating from the tall mugs and shot glasses held by most
of the patrons. A grinning band, strumming out a danceable tune, thump their
feet to the steady beat of the music, stopping only to add to the spitoon. An
empty table and a few stools are available near the bar.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
Someone has spinkled sawdust across this wooden floor. Here and there it has
congealed into disgusting little clumps where people have missed the spitoon.
Footprints in the dust is evidence of the dancing that has recently taken place
in this western saloon.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The long brass railing skirts the bottom of the bar.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB LEAN 1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You rest your leg on the railing. You think you look cool.
   ECHO OTHERS %N strikes a pose.
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
The bar stretches the length of the room. You can see your reflection in the
polished wood top, but the sides are a bit scuffed from peoples' feet.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
The bar's offerings are written here.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 3
The sign reads:

      Beer           25 cents a glass
      Whiskey        1 dollar a shot
      SlimJims       10 cents each

*DESCRIPTION_END

IFTOUCH 3
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The sign is out of reach in its position behind the bar.
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
The band consists of four rather scraggly musicicans. There's Bill on drums,
Beau on piano, Billy Bob on guitar and Floyd on kazoo.

Bill is, to put it politely, portly. He sits in back of the drums on a small
stool in a dirty plaid shirt that leaves an an excellent view of his ample butt
crack. Beads of sweat run down his face as he wails away on the drums, nearly
in rhythm.

Beau is as skinny as a rail with messy black hair and a long scraggly beard. He
bobs his head up and down intensly with his eyes closed as he pounds away on
the keys piano.

Billy Bob is a handsome devil and he knows it. He gyrates around on the tiny
stage, winking at the girls with his baby blue eyes and smiling rakishly as he
stares down any nearby cleavage.

Floyd appears to be in an altered state of conciousness as he hums through the
kazoo, his eyes shut and face relaxed as if in a trance. He apparently takes
kazoo playing very seriously.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFTOUCH 4
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER A large gorilla of a man steps out of nowhere, successfully blocking your
   ECHO PLAYER access to the stage.
   ECHO OTHERS %N makes toward stage, but a large gorilla of a man steps out of nowhere, blocking %h way.
   IFVAR GEN = 0
      ECHO PLAYER Billy Bob and the rest of the band frown at you.
      ECHO OTHERS Billy Bob and the band give %n a dirty look.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR GEN = 1
      ECHO PLAYER Billy bob and the band smiles at you appreciatively.
      ECHO OTHERS Billy Bob and the band smile at %N appreciatively.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 5
This is one of the many chest-high tables scattered around the saloon. They
are comfortable for either sitting or standing at.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 7
The seats of the tall wooden stools are hard, but they do spin around.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB TURN 7
   IFVAR POSITION = 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You spin yourself around on the bar stool.
      ECHO OTHERS %N spins around on the bar stool.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 8
It looks like a large brass vase. Wisely, you avoid looking in it.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFSAY BILLY_BOB!
   ECHO ALL Billy Bob responds by yelling, "Yeeeehaw!" and wiggling his hips."
ENDIF

IFSAY BILL!
   ECHO ALL Bill goes wild on drums!
ENDIF

IFSAY FLOYD!
   ECHO ALL The band goes quiet as Floyd launches into a kazoo solo.
ENDIF

IFSAY BEAU!
   ECHO ALL Beau bangs out a series of arpeggios.
ENDIF

IFSAY BILLY_BOB
   ECHO ALL Billy Bob responds by yelling, "Yeeeehaw!" and wiggling his hips."
ENDIF

