IFPREVERB SIT -1
   IFVAR POSITION ! 1
      CLEARVERB
      IFVAR FLAG1 > 0
         ECHO PLAYER You stop dancing and take a seat on one of the tall stools.
         ECHO OTHERS %N stops dancing and sits down.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
         ECHO PLAYER You hop up onto a bar stool.
         ECHO OTHERS %N hops up onto a bar stool.
      ENDIF
      EQUAL FLAG1 0
      POSITION SIT
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LAY -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You think about laying on the floor...then you think again.
   ECHO OTHERS %N looks like %s might pass out from the drink soon.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB KNEEL -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You think about kneeling on the dirty floor... then you think again.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB STAND -1
   IFVAR POSITION = 1
      CLEARVERB
      POSITION STAND
      ECHO PLAYER You slide down off the bar stool.
      ECHO OTHERS %N slides down off the bar stool.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY LEAVE_PROGRAM
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM < 2
      ECHO PLAYER A soft voice from nowhere in tones, "You are on the only inhabitant of this
      ECHO PLAYER holodeck program. To leave, please say END PROGRAM and then exit the holodeck.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 1
      ECHO PLAYER A swirling light begins to surround you. When it fades, you find you are no
      ECHO PLAYER longer where you were before...
      ECHO OTHERS A swirling light begins to surround %N. When it fades, %s is no longer there.
      MOVE 1920
      AFFECT 1920
      ECHO OTHERS You hear a low hum, and then %N appears surrounded by a swirling light that soon fades.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY END_PROGRAM
   ECHO ALL The scene fades instantly away...
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   EQUAL EXIT 3484
   CALL 38
ENDIF
;
;
;SECLUDED GROVE (Holodeck Program)
NUMBER 3485
NAME Secluded Grove
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CAFE
MOVEMENT_ASTRAL
CHANNEL 777

CALL 49

RELOGIN 1920

ITEM 0 1557 ADJ1=87
ITEM 1 229 ADJ1=317 ADJ2=234
ITEM 2 395 ADJ1=443

EXIT ABOVE 3486

*DESCRIPTION_START
Your hearing is overwhelmed by the almost deafening thunder claps in the dark
sky all around you. Large droplets of water, shaken from the tall pines and
evergreens by the gusting winds, mingle with a steady downpour of warm spring
rain. Lightning flashes through the leaves above you, highlighting everything
for a brief second in a brilliant white flash of light. A smooth moss covered
log lies sheltered beneath one of the heavily leafed pines, surrounded by a
scattering of pine needles mounded up near a small opening in a heavy thicket.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
It looks as though there could be a small area beyond the opening, but it is
too low to walk through.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB GO 0
   ECHO PLAYER The opening is very low, you will need to duck to get through it.
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The lower trunk of this enormous conifer tree is still mostly dry, protected
from the storm by its heavily needled upper limbs.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
The moss appears to have formed a nice cushioned cover on the log, a good
place to relax and watch the falling rain.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB TOUCH 2
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The log feels dry and sturdy under its thick covering of spongy green moss.
   ECHO OTHERS %N sinks %h fingers into the soft green moss covering the log.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB DUCK -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You get down on all fours and crawl through the dark opening.
   ECHO OTHERS %N gets down on all fours and ducks through the dark opening.
   POSITION KNEEL
   DISBAND
   MOVE 3486
   AFFECT 3486
   ECHO OTHERS %N crawls in through the dark opening.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SIT -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR POSITION = 0
      ECHO PLAYER You take a seat on the log.
      ECHO OTHERS %N sits on the log.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You're already sitting.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You sit up.
      ECHO OTHERS %N sits up.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 3
      ECHO PLAYER You take a seat on the log.
      ECHO OTHERS %N sits on the log.
   ENDIF
   POSITION SIT   
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LAY -1
   IFVAR POSITION ! 2
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You lay down on the pine needle carpet.
      ECHO OTHERS %N lays down on the pine needle carpet.
      POSITION LAY
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LISTEN -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You hear the muffled sounds of animal hiding from the rain.
      ECHO PLAYER %N tilts %h head to one side to listen.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SNIFF -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The smell the fresh scent of a summer thunderstorm.
   ECHO OTHERS %N sniffs.
ENDIF

IFSAY LEAVE_PROGRAM
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM < 2
      ECHO PLAYER A soft voice from nowhere in tones, "You are on the only inhabitant of this
      ECHO PLAYER holodeck program. To leave, please say END PROGRAM and then exit the holodeck.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 1
      ECHO PLAYER A swirling light begins to surround you. When it fades, you find you are no
      ECHO PLAYER longer where you were before...
      ECHO OTHERS A swirling light begins to surround %N. When it fades, %s is no longer there.
      MOVE 1920
      AFFECT 1920
      ECHO OTHERS You hear a low hum, and then %N appears surrounded by a swirling light that soon fades.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY END_PROGRAM
   ECHO ALL The scene fades instantly away...
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   EQUAL EXIT 3485
   CALL 38
ENDIF
