;
;
;UNDERSEA (Holodeck Program)
NUMBER 3488
NAME Undersea
REGION 1
UNDERSEA
FIXED_LIGHT
CAFE
MOVEMENT_ASTRAL
CHANNEL 777

CALL 49

RELOGIN 1920

ITEM 0 380 ADJ1=425
ITEM 1 1774
ITEM 2 337 ADJ1=281
ITEM 3 1029
ITEM 4 198 VAL2=100
ITEM 6 1557

*DESCRIPTION_START
Gaily colored fish dart in and out of the huge anemones that have latched on
to the coral here. An old rotting ship lays on the ocean floor, Its mast broken
and its hull layed open to the sea. From deep within, a pair of glowing eyes
surveys you keenly. Every where you look, the area is teaming with life, from
the thousands of varied crabs scurrying hither and thither, to the sea plants
gracully swaying in the ocean currents.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
These bright orange fish are known as garabaldi, their young a more bright
bluish color with orange spots. The clownfish lay amond the tenticles of the
anemones, and trigger fish poke aroundthe sand for morsels. Here and there on
the rocks you can see starfish clinging along the mussles and clams.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
Once a forty foot sloop, it is now a foundation for the newly forming coral.
Its mast has been broken off cruelly near the deck, its hull not much more than
a gaping opening. Its once strong rigging is tangled in sea weed and is barely
visible above the silt. Hardly an inch of its surface remains clear of some
kind of growth, but you can still make out a name on the hull -- "Caliopsis."
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM IN 1
Peering into the gaping hull, you see a giant moray eel staring back at you
from deep within the bowels of the ship. An intact case of wine bottles lays
within, well guarded by this fierce sea serpent.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
Among the many green sea weeds, you recognize the giant kelp as one growing
from a sort of floating root ball in long strands up to the surface. There is
also some grasses, and when you look closely amond their blades, you discern a
tiny sea horse.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFTOUCH 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER They avoid you.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GET 3
   CLEARVERB
   IFNOITEM 5
      EQUAL ROUNDTIME 20
      ECHO PLAYER You swim into the ship to grab the case of wine...
      ECHO OTHERS %N swims into the ship to grab the case of wine...
      PLREVENT 2
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO PLAYER You swim deeper into the ship and slowly up to the eel...
      ECHO OTHERS %N swims deeper into the ship and slowly up to the eel...
      PLREVENT 2
      CONTPLREVENT
      RANDOM DUMMY2 1 4 0
      IFVAR DUMMY2 ! 1
         ECHO PLAYER The eel tries to eat you! You barely escape with your life.
         ECHO OTHERS The eel tries to eat %i! %S barely escapes with %h life.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY2 = 1
         ECHO PLAYER You manage to evade the eel and snag a bottle of wine!
         ECHO OTHERS %N successfully snags a bottle of wine.
         NEWITEM 5 158 VAL5=9
         NEWPUT 5 237 ADJ1=259 VAL2=10
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
   IFITEM 5
      ECHO PLAYER Since you already have one untouched bottle, why risk you neck for another.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFTOUCH 3
   IFVAR ROUNDTIME = 0
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You'll have to wrestle past that eel first.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB DRINK 4
   ECHO PLAYER You sample a swig of salty swill and swiftly spit it out. Yech! Awful! Why did you do that?
   ECHO OTHERS %N samples a swig of salty swill and swiftly spits it out.
   CLEARVERB
ENDIF

IFPREVERB KICK 4
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You swim around a bit.
   ECHO OTHERS %N swims around a bit.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SLAP 4
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You take a few strokes through the water.
   ECHO OTHERS %N takes a few strokes through the water.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 6
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER As you swim toward the opening, a moray eel darts out, snapping at you!
   ECHO OTHERS As %N swims toward the opening, a moray eel darts out, snapping at %i!
ENDIF

POSITION STAND

IFPREVERB LISTEN -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You hear the same sound you hear when you hold a seashell to you ear, it was the sound of the sea,
just like the old wives' tale said.
      ECHO OTHERS %N listens to %h surroundings.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SNIFF -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You snort in some water and practically drown!
   ECHO OTHERS %N snorts in some water and practically drowns!
ENDIF

IFPREVERB CURSE -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER Yes, you can do _that_ underwater.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB KNEEL -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You bring your knees up which cause you to tumble in a backwards somersault.
   ECHO OTHERS %N tumbles over and over in the water.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SIT -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You bring your knees up which cause you to tumble in a backwards somersault.
   ECHO OTHERS %N tumbles over and over in the water.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LAY -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You try to lay down on the ocean bottom, but keep floating back up.
   ECHO OTHERS %N is trying to lay on the ocean bottom, but %s keeps floating up.
ENDIF

IFSAY ASDFJWEOSIFUAOASSF
   POSITION STAND
ELSE
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
      EQUAL FLAG1 1
      PLREVENT 1
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO PLAYER You suddenly wonder how it is you can actually breathe and talk underwater.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY LEAVE_PROGRAM
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM < 2
      ECHO PLAYER A soft voice from nowhere in tones, "You are on the only inhabitant of this
      ECHO PLAYER holodeck program. To leave, please say END PROGRAM and then exit the holodeck.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 1
      ECHO PLAYER A swirling light begins to surround you. When it fades, you find you are no
      ECHO PLAYER longer where you were before...
      ECHO OTHERS A swirling light begins to surround %N. When it fades, %s is no longer there.
      MOVE 1920
      AFFECT 1920
      ECHO OTHERS You hear a low hum, and then %N appears surrounded by a swirling light that soon fades.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY END_PROGRAM
   ECHO ALL The scene fades instantly away...
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   EQUAL EXIT 3488
   CALL 38
ENDIF
