ITEM 3 229 ADJ1=178
EXTEND 3 spreading over the pond
ITEM 4 661
ITEM 5 662
ITEM 6 344 ADJ1=1123 VAL2=3490

; 0 = WATER
; 1 = POND
; 2 = BOULDER
; 3 = TREE
; 4 = FERNS
; 5 = BROMELIAD
; 6 = WATERFALL

;FLAG1 = 0 STANDING
;FLAG1 = 1 IN TREE
;FAGL1 = 2 IN pond

*DESCRIPTION_START
Crystal clear rivulets of water dance against huge algae covered rocks and then
flows down the face of a waterfall to splash into a rippling pound at its base.
Lush tender leafed ferns sprout from the soft grass covered earth while small
heavily leafed shrubs surround the pond, clinging to the rocky crevices. Large
shade trees spread out over several smooth flat boulders that lay just beyond
the shimmering curtain of water, and provide shade from the summer sun.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
You see crystal clear blue water, alive with zillions of bubbles made by the
rushing falls.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFTOUCH 0
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER All you have to do is jump.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SLAP 0
   IFVAR FLAG1 ! 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You playfully splash some water around.
      ECHO OTHERS %N playfully splashes you with some water!
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PLAY 0
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You play in the water, splashing about, blowing bubbles and being silly.
      ECHO OTHERS %N starts splashing around the pond, blowing bubbles and being silly.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
      CLEARVERB
      IFVAR POSITION = 0
         ECHO PLAYER You play along the surface of the water with your toes.
         ECHO OTHERS %N plays along the surface of the water with %h toes.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR POSITION ! 0
         ECHO PLAYER You dangle your arm in the water of the pond.
         ECHO OTHERS %N dangles %h arm in the water.
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 0
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You're already in the pond.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You step down into the pond.
      ECHO OTHERS %N steps down into the pond.
      EQUAL FLAG1 1
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB KICK 0
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You kick your feet, slowly propelling yourself around the pond.
      ECHO OTHERS %N kicks around the pond.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB WAVE 0
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You wave your hands like little fins, and paddle slowly about the pond.
      ECHO OTHERS %N paddles liesurely around the pond.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
Amid a circle of boulders beneath the falls, this shallow pond has formed.
Smooth clean granite lines the bottom so the water stays clear, except for the
zillions of bubbles racing toward the surface.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFTOUCH 1
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER All you have to do is jump.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 1
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You're already in the pond.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You step down into the pond.
      ECHO OTHERS %N steps down into the pond.
      EQUAL FLAG1 1
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB KICK 1
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You kick your feet, slowly propelling yourself around the pond.
      ECHO OTHERS %N kicks around the pond.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB WAVE 1
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 2
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You wave your hands like little fins, and paddle slowly about the pond.
      ECHO OTHERS %N paddles liesurely around the pond.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
The boulders are gray sedimentary rock. Where they are chipped or broken you
can see their layers. Time and running water have made them smooth and flat.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFTOUCH 2
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You can't reach that while in the tree.
   ENDIF
