;
;
;WATERFALL CAVERN
NUMBER 3490
NAME Waterfall Cavern
REGION 1
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CAFE
MOVEMENT_ASTRAL
CHANNEL 777

CALL 49

RELOGIN 1920
EXIT O 3489

ITEM 0 344 VAL2=3489
ITEM 1 363 ADJ1=183
ITEM 2 368 ADJ2=183
ITEM 3 277 ADJ1=312
EXTEND 3 covered with spongy moss
PUT 3 1690 ADJ1=1344 VAL5=666

*DESCRIPTION_START
Just enough light filters through the cascade of water to brighten this large
cavern. Its stone surfaces are very wet and slippery from the constant spray of
the waterfall, several long stalagmites and stalactites making maneuvering next
to impossible. A stone shelf covered with spongy moss seems to be the only dry
place to sit or lay.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
An almost solid curtain of water, it completely covers the cavern opening,
blocking both the view from the inside and out. It seems even louder on this
side of the majestic waterfall, its thounderous roar echoing from stalagmite
to stalagtite.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFTOUCH 0
   IFVAR POSITION ! 0
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You can't reach that from here.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB TOUCH 0
   IFVAR POSITION = 0
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You run your fingers through the curtain of water.
      ECHO OTHERS %N runs %h fingers through the waterfall.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You step through the waterfall.
   ECHO OTHERS %N steps through the waterfall.
   AFFECT 3489
   ECHO OTHERS %N arrives through a waterfall.
   MOVE 3489
   POSITION LAY
   EQUAL FLAG1 2
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
Over several decades, dripping water has left behind stone icicles that both
hang down from the ceiling and stretch up from the floor of this cavern, a few
here and there meeting in the middle.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
Over several decades, dripping water has left behind stone icicles that both
hang down from the ceiling and stretch up from the floor of this cavern, a few
here and there meeting in the middle.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
In a corner of the cavern, a stone shelf juts out between two walls. Covered
in a thick layer of spongy moss, it looks both dry and relatively comfortable.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB GO 3
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR POSITION ! 0
      ECHO PLAYER You're already on the stone shelf.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 0
      ECHO PLAYER You hop up on the stone shelf.
      ECHO OTHERS %N hops up on the stone shelf.
      POSITION SIT
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GET -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 1690
      IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 666
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER You pull some spongy moss off the stone shelf.
         ECHO OTHERS %N pulls some spongy moss off the stone shelf.
         NEWITEM -1 1690 ADJ1=1344 VAL2=1 VAL3=403 VAL5=9
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PULL -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 1690
      IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 666
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER You pull some spongy moss off the stone shelf.
         ECHO OTHERS %N pulls some spongy moss off the stone shelf.
         NEWITEM -1 1690 ADJ1=1344 VAL2=1 VAL3=403 VAL5=9
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB EAT -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 1690
      IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 666
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER Why not pull off some moss from the stone shelf before you try to eat it?
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SIT -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR POSITION = 0
      ECHO PLAYER You hop up on the stone shelf.
      ECHO OTHERS %N hops up on the stone shelf.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You're already sitting.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You sit up.
      ECHO OTHERS %N sits up.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You hop up on the stone shelf.
      ECHO OTHERS %N hops up on the stone shelf.
   ENDIF
   POSITION SIT
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LAY -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR POSITION ! 2
      ECHO PLAYER You stretch out on the stone shelf.
      ECHO OTHERS %N stretches out on the stone shelf.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You're already laying down.
   ENDIF
   POSITION LAY
ENDIF

IFPREVERB KNEEL -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The stalagmites make it impossible to kneel anywhere.
ENDIF

IFSAY LEAVE_PROGRAM
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM < 2
      ECHO PLAYER A soft voice from nowhere in tones, "You are on the only inhabitant of this
      ECHO PLAYER holodeck program. To leave, please say END PROGRAM and then exit the holodeck.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 1
      ECHO PLAYER A swirling light begins to surround you. When it fades, you find you are no
      ECHO PLAYER longer where you were before...
      ECHO OTHERS A swirling light begins to surround %N. When it fades, %s is no longer there.
      MOVE 1920
      AFFECT 1920
      ECHO OTHERS You hear a low hum, and then %N appears surrounded by a swirling light that soon fades.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY END_PROGRAM
   ECHO ALL The scene fades instantly away...
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   EQUAL EXIT 3489
   CALL 38
ENDIF
;
;
;ARABIAN NIGHTS
NUMBER 3491
NAME Arabian Nights
REGION 1
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CAFE
MOVEMENT_ASTRAL
CHANNEL 777

CALL 49

RELOGIN 1920
EXIT ABOVE 3492

ITEM 0 605 ADJ1=286 ADJ2=1037
ITEM 1 1035 ADJ1=222 ADJ2=925
ITEM 2 413 ADJ1=67

*DESCRIPTION_START
An expansive waste stretches out behind you, nothing to be seen but mile after
mile of sand glittering in the moonlight. In front of you, bursting up from the
desert like the ancient stone walls of some half-buried fortress, a sheer rock
face rises into the darkness of the nighttime sky.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB EXAM 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER Nearly a vertical wall of stone, it rises several hundred feet into the air,
   ECHO PLAYER vanishing into the darkness above. There's just enough moonlight to make out
   ECHO PLAYER some old etched writing in the side of the rock face, obscured by the scouring
   IFITEM 3
      ECHO PLAYER wind-blown sand. A large cave leads deep inside the rock face.
   ENDIF
   IFNOITEM 3
      ECHO PLAYER wind-blown sand.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 0
There's just enough moonlight to make out a few crudely etched letters...

Ali Baba was here.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB CLIMB 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You attempt to climb the rock face, but your hands and feet find no purchase.
   ECHO OTHERS %N tries in vain to climb the sheer rock face.
ENDIF

IFVERB LEAN 0
   RANDOM DUMMY1 1 10 0
   IFVAR DUMMY1 = 10
      ECHO PLAYER You feel something on the rock face shift beneath your back.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFVERB PUSH 0
   RANDOM DUMMY1 1 10 0
   IFVAR DUMMY1 = 10
      ECHO PLAYER You feel it budge just a little.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFVERB KNOCK 0
   ECHO ALL It sounds hollow.
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
There's just enough moonlight to make out a few crudely etched letters...

Ali Baba was here.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 1
There's just enough moonlight to make out a few crudely etched letters...

Ali Baba was here.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB GET 2
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You scoop up a handful of sand, letting it sift through your fingers.
   ECHO OTHERS %N scoops up a handful of sand, letting it sift through %h fingers.
   RANDOM DUMMY1 1 100 0
   IFVAR DUMMY1 = 100
      ECHO PLAYER You find a valuable gem in the sand!
      ECHO OTHERS %N finds a valuable gem in the sand!
      NEWITEM -1 1538 ADJ1=275 VAL1=300
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PLAY 2
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The sand is too dry to make a sand castle with.
   ECHO OTHERS %N tries to build a sand castle, but the sand won't stick.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SIT -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR POSITION = 0
      ECHO PLAYER You sit down on the cool sand.
      ECHO OTHERS %N sits down on the cool sand.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You're already sitting.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You sit up.
      ECHO OTHERS %N sits up.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 3
      ECHO PLAYER You sit down on the cool sand.
      ECHO OTHERS %N sits down on the cool sand.
   ENDIF
   POSITION SIT
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LAY -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR POSITION = 0
      ECHO PLAYER You lay down on the cool sand.
      ECHO OTHERS %N lays down on the cool sand.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You lay back on the cool sand.
      ECHO OTHERS %N lays back on the cool sand.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You're already laying down.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION = 3
      ECHO PLAYER You lay down on the cool sand.
      ECHO OTHERS %N lays down on the cool sand.
   ENDIF
   POSITION LAY
ENDIF

