;
;
;Treasure Trove
NUMBER 3492
NAME Treasure Trove
REGION 1
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CAFE
MOVEMENT_ASTRAL
CHANNEL 777

CALL 49

RELOGIN 1920

ITEM 0 373 ADJ1=526 LIT
ITEM 1 916
EXTEND 1 of gold and silver coins
PUT 1 161 ADJ1=147 ADJ2=592 ADJ3=292
PUT 1 968 ADJ1=468 VAL5=666
PUT 1 1084 ADJ1=579 ADJ2=147 VAL5=666
PUT 1 138 ADJ1=141 ADJ2=114 VAL5=666
PUT 1 1213 ADJ1=487 ADJ2=39 VAL5=666
ITEM 2 1668
EXTEND 2 of pearls
ITEM 3 468
EXTEND 3 of solid gold eggs
ITEM 4 386 ADJ1=663
PUT 4 387
ITEM 5 1565 ADJ1=539 ADJ2=32
ITEM 6 1181 ADJ1=695 ADJ2=973
EXTEND 6 with tattered tassels woven at each corner
ITEM 7 1308 ADJ1=222
ITEM 8 346 ADJ1=187

*DESCRIPTION_START
Glittering brilliantly from nearby torchlight, a virtual mountain of treasure
fills this enormous cavern. A magnificent candelabra rises triumphantly from a
gargantuan mound of gold and silver coins, while long strings of pearls drape
various objets d'art. A golden harp rests near a large nest of solid gold eggs,
juxtaposed by a simple, unadorned brass lamp. The air is crisp, and the sound
of mineral rich water occasionally dripping from centuries-old stalactites in
neighboring caves can be eerily heard.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
It juts from the wall in a brass sconce, flooding this cavern with a bright
but flickering light. On the stone wall beside it, someone has etched the words
"Foxy was here."
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB UNLIGHT 0
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You extinguish the burning torch.
   ECHO OTHERS %N extinguishes the burning torch.
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   ECHO ALL It magically relights itself!
ENDIF

IFVERB PULL 0
   IFITEM 9
      ECHO ALL You hear a slight grinding noise.
   ENDIF
   IFNOITEM 9
      NEWITEM 9 1829 VAL2=3491
      ECHO PLAYER You hear a low rumble as a large crevice begins to form, opening out into a
      ECHO PLAYER cave that leads back outside.
      AFFECT 3491
      ECHO ALL You hear a low rumble as a large crevice begins to form in the once seamless sheer rock face. Slowly
opening ever wider, the entrance to a vast cave is revealed beyond.
      NEWITEM 3 1829 VAL2=3492
   ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
This gargantuan mound of coins seems to go on forever, creating an ocean of
opulence that covers the entire floor of the cavern. You have a sudden desire
to jump in and take a swim!
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
Each length is hand knotted and bears perfecly round, natural pearls. They
drape over several old portraits, a gem-encrusted chalice, a marble statue, and
a beautiful bronze hourglass.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB TOUCH 2
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You run your hands across a string of pearls.
   ECHO OTHERS %N runs %h hands across a string of pearls.
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
This rather large nest is filled with solid gold goose eggs. An intricately
colored carpet with tattered tassels woven at each corner is stretched out in
front of it.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM IN 3
It is filled to overflowing with solid gold goose eggs.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB GO 3
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER Your maternal instincts taking over, you roost upon the nest, fidgeting 'til
   ECHO PLAYER you are comfortable and are able to manage to swathe the eggs in the warm folds
   ECHO PLAYER of your behind. An uncontrollable cluck escapes your lips.
   ECHO OTHERS %N sits upon the nest and begins clucking.
   POSITION SIT
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
It holds eighteen candles and can could easily illuminate the dimmest of
dark gloomy mansions.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB LIGHT 4
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 0
      ECHO PLAYER You light the eighteen candles on the candelabra, and light floods the
      ECHO PLAYER cavern, causing you to shield your eyes for a moment while they adjust.
      ECHO OTHERS %N lights the eighteen candles on the candelabra, and light floods the cavern, causing you to shield
your eyes for a moment while they adjust.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER The candelabra is already lit.
   ENDIF
   EQUAL ITEMVAL5 1
ENDIF

IFPREVERB UNLIGHT 4
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 0
      ECHO PLAYER The candelabra is not lit.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You extinguish the candelabra, and the light returns to its shadowy state.
      ECHO OTHERS %N extinguishes the candelabra, and the light returns to its shadowy state.
   ENDIF
   EQUAL ITEMVAL5 0
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GO 4
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You jump over the candelabra...
   ECHO OTHERS %N jumps over the candelabra...
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   RANDOM DUMMY1 1 2 0
   IFVAR DUMMY1 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER ... Nimble and quick, you gracefully land on your feet, sinking into the treasure up to your knees.
      ECHO OTHERS ... Nimble and quick, %s gracefully lands on %h feet, sinking into the treasure up to %h knees.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR DUMMY1 = 2
      ECHO PLAYER ... Clumsily you catch your foot on an arm of the candelabra and tumble down the side of the
treasure mound!
      ECHO OTHERS ... Clumsily %s catches %h foot on an arm of the candelabra and tumbles down the side of the
treasure mound!
   ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 5
It looks like it might feel smooth.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB OPEN 5
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You lift the small stopper from the lamp and spy a tiny blue genie in the
   ECHO PLAYER lamp bathing! He screams in surprise, and his arm reaches out and snatches the
   ECHO PLAYER stopper from you, closing the lamp.
   ECHO OTHERS %N lifts the small stopper from the lamp and peeks inside.
   ECHO OTHERS You hear a startled scream, then a large blue hand reaches through the opening, grabs the stopper and
closes the lamp!
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LISTEN 5
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You hear rattling inside!
   ECHO OTHERS %N presses %h ear to the side of the lamp.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB TOUCH 5
   CLEARVERB
   RANDOM DUMMY1 1 3 0
   IFVAR DUMMY1 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You rub the lamp, and a cloud of smoke billows out, congealing into the form
      ECHO PLAYER of a blue genie! He discontinues his pedicure long enough to give you a nasty
      ECHO PLAYER look before he retreats back into the lamp!
      ECHO OTHERS %N rubs the lamp, and a cloud of smoke billows out, congealing into the form of a blue genie! He
discontinues his pedicure long enough to give you a nasty look before he retreats back into the lamp!
   ENDIF
   IFVAR DUMMY1 = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You rub the lamp, and a cloud of smoke billows out, congealing into the form
      ECHO PLAYER of a blue genie, his face covered with an oatmeal masque and his eyes covered
      ECHO PLAYER by cucumber slices. With an irritated wave of his hand, he disperses back into
      ECHO PLAYER the lamp!
      ECHO OTHERS %N rubs the lamp, and a cloud of smoke billows out, congealing into the form of a blue genie, his
face covered with an oatmeal masque and his eyes covered by cucumber slices. With an irritated wave of his hand, he
disperses back into the lamp!
   ENDIF
   IFVAR DUMMY1 = 3
      ECHO PLAYER You rub the lamp, and a cloud of smoke billows out, congealing into the form
      ECHO PLAYER of a blue genie wearing a bathrobe and slippers with his hair wrapped up in a
      ECHO PLAYER bath towel. Without putting down his Harlequinn Romance, he saunters back into
      ECHO PLAYER the lamp!
      ECHO OTHERS %N rubs the lamp, and a cloud of smoke billows out, congealing into the form of a blue genie wearing
a bathrobe and slippers with his hair wrapped up in a bath towel. Without putting down his Harlequinn Romance, he
saunters back into the lamp!
   ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 6
Though you are certain it was once a magnificently woven carpet, its threads
have become worn and its tassels tattered.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB GO 6
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER It's still in the air!
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 0
      EQUAL ITEMVAL1 1
      ECHO PLAYER You step onto the carpet.
      ECHO OTHERS %N steps onto the carpet.
      ECHO ALL It immediately lifts into the air and begins soaring around the room, dodging around stalagmites and
low-hanging stalactites.
      PLREVENT 1
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO PLAYER It suddenly rears up, tossing you onto the mound of coins!
      ECHO OTHERS It suddenly rears up, tossing %N onto the mound of coins!
      POSITION LAY
      PLREVENT 1
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL It slowly drifts back down to rest in front of the nest of golden eggs.
      SETITEMVAL 6 1 0
   ENDIF
ENDIF

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 7
You admire a large portrait of a full figured woman with long-flowing bright
red hair wearing many accessories.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 8
You see a marble statue of a handsome, muscular man bearing no fig leaf.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB LISTEN -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER The air is still and absolutely silent, save for an occassional drip.
      ECHO OTHERS %N listens to %h surroundings.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SNIFF -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER An earthy, mineral smell permeates the air.
      ECHO OTHERS %N sniffs.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB SIT -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR POSITION = 1
      ECHO PLAYER You're already sitting.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION ! 1
      ECHO PLAYER You make a place for yourself amongst the treasure.
      ECHO OTHERS %N takes a seat amongst the treasure.
      POSITION SIT
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LAY -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR POSITION = 2
      ECHO PLAYER You're already laying down.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR POSITION ! 2
      ECHO PLAYER You lay back in the mound of gold and silver coins.
      ECHO OTHERS %N lays back in the mound of gold and silver coins.
      POSITION LAY
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GAZE -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You gaze about in wonderment at the unbelievable specatacle before you.
      ECHO OTHERS %N gazes about the area.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB JUMP -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You dive head-first into the mound of gold and silver coins, swimming in its
   ECHO PLAYER shifting riches.
   ECHO OTHERS %N dives head-first into the mound of gold and silver coins, swimming in its shifting riches.
   POSITION LAY
ENDIF

IFPREVERB EXAM -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 161
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER The fabulous wealth represented by the millions of coins staggers your mind.
      ECHO OTHERS %N stares at the millions of coins, a gleam of greed shining in %h eyes.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 138
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER A gem-encrusted chalice catches your eye.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 1213
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER A beautiful bronze hourglass drains crimson sand from one end to the other.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 968
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER The artisanship of this great instrument is unsurpassed.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 1084
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER Though made of solid gold, from its size and shape you can easily tell that
      ECHO PLAYER it's from a goose.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB READ -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 1035
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You read, "Foxy was here!"
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB GET -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 161
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You scoop up armfuls of gold and silver coins, letting them spill all over
      ECHO PLAYER you in a shower of sheer opulence.
      ECHO OTHERS %N scoops up armfuls of gold and silver coins, letting them shower down on top of %i.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 666
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You can't take that.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB EAT -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 161
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER What did your mother tell you about putting dirty money in your mouth?!
      ECHO OTHERS %N exhibits the poorest of personal hygeine and licks some gold and silver coins. Who knows where
those dirty things have been?!
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 1084
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You bite into a solid gold egg and chip a tooth!
      ECHO OTHERS %N bites into a solid gold egg and chips a tooth!
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LICK -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 161
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER What did your mother tell you about putting dirty money in your mouth?!
      ECHO OTHERS %N exhibits the poorest of personal hygeine and licks some gold and silver coins. Who knows where
those dirty things have been?!
    ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB TICKLE -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 968
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You tickle the harp and it giggles!
      ECHO OTHERS %N tickles the harp and it giggles!
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB KISS -1
   IFVAR ARCHNUM = 968
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You kiss the harp and it giggles!
      ECHO OTHERS %N kisses the harp and it giggles!
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY LEAVE_PROGRAM
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM < 2
      ECHO PLAYER A soft voice from nowhere in tones, "You are on the only inhabitant of this
      ECHO PLAYER holodeck program. To leave, please say END PROGRAM and then exit the holodeck.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 1
      ECHO PLAYER A swirling light begins to surround you. When it fades, you find you are no
      ECHO PLAYER longer where you were before...
      ECHO OTHERS A swirling light begins to surround %N. When it fades, %s is no longer there.
      MOVE 1920
      AFFECT 1920
      ECHO OTHERS You hear a low hum, and then %N appears surrounded by a swirling light that soon fades.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY END_PROGRAM
   ECHO ALL The scene fades instantly away...
   PLREVENT 1
   CONTPLREVENT
   IFITEM 9
      REMOVEITEM 9
   ENDIF
   AFFECT 3491
   IFITEM 3
      REMOVEITEM 3
   ENDIF
   EQUAL EXIT 3491
   CALL 38
ENDIF
